{"name": "schemantis-cli", "metadata": {"name": "schemantis-cli", "version": "0.0.5", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A python comand line tool that integrates with schemantis", "upload_time": 1733491983}, "documentation": ["\n# Schemantis CLI\n\n## Introduction\n\nThe Schemantis CLI is a command-line interface tool that allows you to generate code from map data using the Schemantis API.\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install the Schemantis CLI, you can use pip:\n\n```bash\npip install schemantis-cli\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nTo use the Schemantis CLI, you need to provide the following arguments:\n\n- `--generator` or `-g`: The generator to use (e.g., 'python').\n- `--map_id_or_name` or `-m`: The map ID or name.\n- `--output-directory` or `-o`: The output directory for the generated code.\n\nHere is an example command to generate Python code from a map:\n\n```bash\nschemantis-cli --generator python --map_id_or_name 123 --output-directory ./out\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "main", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "main.generate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "generator", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "map_id_or_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "output_directory", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "main.configuration", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "main.SCHEMANTIS_API_KEY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "main.api_client", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "main.api_instance", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "main.parser", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "main.args", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "generate_python", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "